.Dd March 1, 2026
.Dt MD 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm md
.Nd extract and manipulate Markdown content
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar command
.Op Fl -json
.Op Ar file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a command-line utility for working with Markdown files.
It parses Markdown leniently, preferring best-effort results over strict errors.
.Pp
If no
.Ar file
is given,
.Nm
reads from standard input.
.Pp
Plain text output is the default.
Use
.Fl -json
for structured output.
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width "frontmatter"
.It Ic body Op Ar file
Output the document body without frontmatter.
.It Ic frontmatter Op Ar file
Output raw YAML frontmatter.
.It Ic frontmatter set Oo Fl i Oc Ar file Ar key Ar value Op Ar key Ar value ...
Set one or more frontmatter fields.
Multiple key-value pairs can be specified.
If the key already exists, its value is replaced.
If no frontmatter exists, one is created.
.Pp
Output goes to standard output by default.
Use
.Fl i
to edit the file in-place.
.It Ic frontmatter delete Oo Fl i Oc Ar file Ar key Op Ar key ...
Delete one or more frontmatter fields.
.Pp
Output goes to standard output by default.
Use
.Fl i
to edit the file in-place.
.It Ic headings Oo Fl -json Oc Op Ar file
List headings with their depth and line numbers.
.It Ic links Oo Fl -json Oc Op Ar file
List outgoing links.
Supports standard Markdown links, Obsidian wikilinks, images, and embeds.
.It Ic links Fl -incoming Oo Fl -json Oc Oo Fl -dir Ar directory Oc Ar file
List incoming links to
.Ar file
by scanning other Markdown files.
Wikilinks are matched by basename.
Standard links are resolved relative to the source file.
.Pp
By default, scans the parent directory of
.Ar file .
Use
.Fl -dir
to specify a different directory.
.It Ic tags Oo Fl -json Oc Op Ar file
Extract inline
.Li #tags
with deduplication.
.It Ic codeblocks Oo Fl -json Oc Op Ar file
List code blocks with language and line ranges.
Supports fenced blocks (backtick and tilde) and indented blocks
(4+ spaces or tab).
.It Ic stats Oo Fl -json Oc Op Ar file
Show word count and line count.
.It Ic section Ar heading Op Ar file
Extract content under a specific heading.
The
.Ar heading
can include depth markers
.Pq e.g., Dq ## API
or just the heading text.
Content includes everything until the next heading of equal or lesser depth.
.El
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -json
Output in JSON format.
.It Fl -help
Show usage information.
.It Fl i
.Pq Ic frontmatter set No and Ic frontmatter delete No only
Edit the file in-place instead of writing to standard output.
.It Fl -incoming
.Pq Ic links No only
Scan for incoming links instead of listing outgoing links.
.It Fl -dir Ar directory
.Pq Ic links --incoming No only
Directory to scan for incoming links.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Extract the body of a Markdown file:
.Dl md body notes.md
.Pp
List headings as JSON:
.Dl md headings --json notes.md | jq '.[] | select(.depth == 2)'
.Pp
Set multiple frontmatter fields in-place:
.Dl md frontmatter set -i notes.md title \(dqMy Note\(dq draft true
.Pp
Delete frontmatter fields:
.Dl md frontmatter delete -i notes.md draft tags
.Pp
Find all files linking to a note:
.Dl md links --incoming notes.md --dir ./vault/
.Pp
Extract a section by heading:
.Dl md section \(dq## API\(dq notes.md
.Pp
Read from stdin:
.Dl cat notes.md | md tags
.Pp
Process all Markdown files in a directory:
.Dl find vault/ -name '*.md' | xargs -I{} md tags {}
.Sh SUPPORTED FORMATS
.Bl -bullet
.It
Standard Markdown links:
.Li [text](url)
.It
Obsidian wikilinks:
.Li [[target]] ,
.Li [[target|alias]]
.It
Image and embed links:
.Li ![alt](url) ,
.Li ![[embed]]
.It
YAML frontmatter (delimited by
.Li --- )
.It
ATX headings
.Pq Li "# H1"
through
.Li "###### H6"
.It
Fenced code blocks (backtick and tilde)
.It
Indented code blocks (4+ spaces or tab)
.It
Inline tags
.Pq Li #tag
.El
